      Solution for "Refused to execute Script"
      If you're getting an error that looks like "Refused to execute script from 'http://localhost:3000/js/libs/jquery-3-1-0%20.min.js' because its MIME type ('text/html') is not executable, and strict MIME type checking is enabled." then it could be because you have your src pointing to the wrong folder. Perhaps you have jQuery instead of jquery. In my case I accidentally saved my jquery file in a folder named "libs " instead of "libs" the difference being an accidental space when i originally named the libs folder.  This meant, that src was looking in a folder that didn't even exists, and could therefore not find the correct file.
